# Desktop session stack — Plasma Mobile, all from Arch Linux ARM (aarch64).
# Plasma Mobile runs on its own compositor (kwin_wayland); NOT hosted in Sway.
#
# build-image.sh installs this list into the rootfs (Phase 4). The pocknix-desktop package ships
# only the launcher/switch scripts — it does NOT depend() on this stack, to keep makepkg from
# dragging the whole KDE/Qt tree into the build chroot (see packages/pocknix-desktop/PKGBUILD).

plasma-mobile        # mobile shell + the startplasmamobile session entrypoint
plasma-workspace     # startplasma-wayland + plasmashell (the shell host)
kwin                 # the Wayland compositor Plasma Mobile runs on
plasma-nano          # minimal shell container the mobile shell builds on
plasma-nm            # Wi-Fi / network applet (touch UI)
powerdevil           # power / brightness / suspend management
plasma-settings      # mobile settings app
kscreen              # kscreen-doctor -> the panel rotation/scale transform (rotated-DSI crux)

# --- app store (Flatpak) ---
# Discover is the native KDE store and ships a Flatpak backend; flatpak provides the runtime.
# Flathub is added by pocknix-flathub.service (pocknix-desktop) on first online boot. A GTK store
# like Bazaar is NOT in Arch repos — install it AS a flatpak from Flathub once this is up.
flatpak              # the Flatpak runtime + CLI
discover             # plasma-discover — KDE app store with the Flatpak backend

# On-screen keyboard: maliit-keyboard is AUR-only (NOT in Arch/ALARM repos) -> needs its own
# pocknix package (build from AUR, like gtk2/inputplumber). Deferred; not needed to validate
# render/rotation. Plasma's built-in virtualkeyboard can be a stopgap. TODO: packages/maliit-keyboard.
# minimal app set — keep lean, no full Plasma desktop
# discover           # optional app store; uncomment if wanted
